reviews.review_text: - A Tomb Thumb's Blues that Michael Palin would have cut short on the grounds that it was far too silly. The Bird Song, apart from the foul effects of their contemporary fascination with MIDI tech, is fiendishly masterful: a really dark, chocolatey-spicey one. Never Trust a Woman falls flat on its face at the end. A hardcore shred-jazz ending jam in Uncle John's that is jaw-dropping. Ditto for the jam in Playin'. Greatest Story is hot. And much more.
